        <section id="fs-id3024684" class="section-summary" type="section-summary">
        <title>Summary</title>
        <para id="import-auto-id2755240">Deviance is a violation of norms. Whether or not something is deviant depends on contextual definitions, the situation, and people’s response to the behavior. Society seeks to limit deviance through the use of sanctions that help maintain a system of social control. Deviance is often relative, and perceptions of it can change quickly and unexpectedly.</para>
</section>

        <section id="fs-id2266112" class="section-quiz" type="section-quiz">
        <title>Section Quiz</title>
 <exercise id="fs-id1370636" type="section-quiz">
<problem id="fs-id1488132">
        <para id="import-auto-id1308884">Which of the following best describes how deviance is defined?</para>
        <list id="fs-id2851000" list-type="enumerated" number-style="lower-alpha">
        <item>Deviance is defined by federal, state, and local laws.</item>
        <item>Deviance’s definition is determined by one’s religion.</item>
        <item>Deviance occurs whenever someone else is harmed by an action.</item>
        <item>Deviance is socially defined.</item>
        </list>
</problem>

<solution id="eip-id1445446">
<label/>

        <para id="eip-id2031159">D</para>
</solution>
</exercise>
<exercise id="fs-id1303155" type="section-quiz">
<problem id="fs-id2308814">
